    "The rest of the paper will examine arguments for and against this stronger version of P1.",
    "This is where the debates in action theory alluded to above become relevant.",
    "Apparent support for a constitutive version of P1 comes from what action theorists sometimes call the 'Anscombe-Davidson principle'.",
    "The principle is usually presented as a way of individuating actions.",
